node.text:
Katie McRose, 26, and her wife Darian travel around Texas to sheer sheep, llamas and alpacas. They founded their business, Right Choice Shearing, in 2019. This year, they expect to bring in at least $80,000 servicing over 575 farms. 

Read more: https://cnb.cx/3AfkSJ2

node.title: Bringing in $80K a year shearing sheep in Texas.

node.text:
While pursuing his dreams, 'Bling Empire's Kevin Kreider says he racked up as much as $26,000 in credit card debt. 

Luckily, the frugal star adjusted his lifestyle so he could have a fresh start in Los Angeles. Here's how he did it.

node.text:
Leonardo "MkLeo" Lopez Perez, 20, is one of the esports industry's top gamers, widely considered to be the world's best player of "Super Smash Bros." 🎮⁠
⁠
But, growing up, Perez's family didn't have a lot of money. "I remember that we used to sell a lot of things just to have money to eat, like [once] a week," he said. ⁠
⁠
Read how playing video games changed his life at the link in our bio.

🚨One-minute money hack🚨
 
Your emergency fund could earn 8 times as much interest in a high-yield savings account. 💸

The average savings account earns an annual percentage yield of around 0.06%, while high-yield accounts currently earn around 0.5% APY.

node.text:
James Park, the CEO and co-founder of Fitbit, discussed the importance of perseverance when starting a new company. 💪⁠
⁠
At the link in our bio, he shared advice for aspiring entrepreneurs, how Covid has influenced his personal fitness routine and what he considers his greatest failures.
